			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A gust of wind can interrupt you in DAoC and you can't be in combat mode while casting. 
<br />

<br />
While the two systems are similar I would have to give higher marks to EQ's magic system overall.
<br />

<br />
Fizzling was frustrating in EQ but it was something you could work your way out of until it wasn't that frustrating anymore.  I have seen no way to work your way out of the way you can be interrupted in DAoC though.
<br />

<br />
There is a nice variety of spells in both games though and DAoC has no spells to memorize so far. 
<br />

<br />
Both games suffer from magic user imbalance which is no surprise.
<br />

<br />
I like the spell effects from both games also.  
<br />

<br />
Many recovery is a plus for DAoC and I'd say it's half of what EQ was if not less.  And to be honest this point alone might be enough to convince some EQ casters to try DAoC.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  
<br />

<br />
I think you'd like the wizard class her if you like a big boom.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  Though someone else can probably compare the two game classes better then I.  
<br />

<br />
Cleric you'll like because of the low downtime but you'll still be called to revive left and right.  
<br />

<br />
I think you'd also be happy with the expanded role of the cleric in DAoC.  Not only can we heal and revive, we can mes and stun also.  
<br />

<br />
Some clerics chose the combat role and become smite clerics who can still heal but they pack a meaner punch in their DD.  
<br />

<br />
Anyway there's pluses and minuses for both games but IMO overall EQ's system is much smoother and player friendly.  But when you break the classes down you might find you like the DAoC class better.  Won't know till you play though &lt;shrugs&gt;      
<br />

<br />
There are a lot of people here who are very knowledgeable about the classes you mentioned though so maybe they'll chip in.  But regardless goodluck with whatever you decide.
<br />

<br />
Pax</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
