			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I must agree with Firehead. My main was an Enchanter, although I did experience many of the caster classes in EQ.
<br />

<br />
Downtime, in comparison to EQ, doesn't exist in DAOC. That's how much better it is. Camping spawns doesn't exist in DAOC. Memming spells doesn't exist in DAOC. You level, you have your new spells. You don't even have to move to go buy them.
<br />

<br />
Graphics of spell effects, come on. Be serious. There is no way EQ comes close to these effects. Case in point, a wizzy's fire bolt or dd, not only do you see a terrific bolt, like in EQ, but unlike EQ, once it hits the mob it's engulfed in fire and when the fire subsides, smoke rises off the mob making it so relistic. It actually looks like you BBQ'd the mob rofl.
<br />

<br />
The biggest difference is, DAOC is totally different than EQ. It will take you a little bit to adjust to it's simplicity. I disagree that EQ is more user friendly. I also thought that at first, but I now attribute that to a learning curve just like the one I'm sure I had when I started EQ eons ago. Everything is much more user friendly.
<br />

<br />
Now if they could fix it where you could sell everything all at once, I'd be even happier.
<br />

<br />
Some caster classes, no, I think all caster classes are different in DAOC. As I said, my main was an enchanter in EQ. DAOC enchanters are absolutely nothing like EQ enchanters. They aren't the kings of mana recovery and crowd control they are in EQ. In fact, after getting to lvl 9ish, I could see it was very little challenge to play and left me foreseeing the boredom ahead. 
<br />

<br />
I switched to a mage for an alt as it turned out, and now have a wizzie as my main. Mages do alot of the crowd control and are an awesome class, but soloing really requires a pet, which mages must acquire like EQ chanters did, by casting on a humanoid, which can sometimes be hard to locate.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion to you would be if you are finding EQ just doesn't do it anymore, like I did when I quit playing it many months ago, I think you would enjoy DAOC. Seeing that the first month is free, I would camp EQ and tryout DAOC for the free month. That way, before doing anything with EQ, you can know yourself which you want to play.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
