			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yep, I had a 58 cleric on EQ and I'm so happy I left for DAoC.  The game is so much more FUN.  There's more action and no waiting 3 hours to get a raid going.  No sit on our asses for 10 minutes so the healer can get their mana back.  
<br />

<br />
Also, DAoC is more about beating the crap out of stuff quickly where as EQ featured minute long fights against every 45+ mob - this means that the nuke classes make a much bigger impact.  In the high end game of EQ, wizzies were easilly outdamaged by rogues and mages were a joke... Half the time your group/raid won't let you cast a pet because it always somehow finds a train to bring to the group thanks to Verant's great pathing system.
<br />

<br />
And spell effects?  They DEFINITELY own EQ's.  In EQ, I turned my spell effects off because they were, for the most part, annoying and boring (ooo  blue balls flying around me... AGAIN) and created lots of lag.  DAoC has some incredible looking effects and there is easilly 4 or 5 unique effects per class... where as there was about 4 or 5 different looking effects in EQ TOTAL.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
