			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far are the graphic effects of spells go, I dont see how there can be a discussion.  We all see the same things (colorblind folk not included), so we all see that DAoC spell effects are more numerous, more realistic, and all around better than EQ's.  We all are entitled to opinions of course, and we should all respect those opinions.  But trying to say that EQ's spell effects are even close to comparing to DAoC's is like trying to say that the earth only goes around the sun once a century - its ludicrous, not opinion.
<br />

<br />
On the topic of fizzles vs. interrupts, I havent found the interrupts to be a problem at all.  If you dont move, you wont be inturrupted.  If a monster is trying to bash your head in, then of course you'll be inturrupted, but with the quickcast ability most casters get, that can be avoided.  The only time this becomes horribly dangerous is if you're trying to solo.  The game is designed for group play, and if stick to groups there'll be more success than soloing.
<br />

<br />
I will say that for a few weeks I had problems with constantly being inturrupted when trying to cast just after standing up, sometimes I'd have to wait 5 seconds after standing to get a spell off.  Perhaps you experienced this too Pax.  I dont know what the prob was, I'm no expert on signals/servers/isp's, but I think that had to be due to some delay effects on information transfer.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
