			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally I much prefer EQ's casting system during fights, and I prefer Daoc's system during downtime.
<br />

<br />
first off fizzles are just fizzles, in doac if a twig falls off a tree next to you you get interrupted.
<br />

<br />
in EQ you can time casts to land between the mobs hits, you can cast with autoattack on, and you can recover after you get hit and continue casting!
<br />

<br />
in doac if the mob is hitting you you only have 2 options A)whip out your trusty stick and try to beat back on the mob, or B) hit dash and run as fast as you can and hope the mob goes away. If you are attacking you cannot cast anything, if you are being hit (or missed even) you cannot cast anything. If you stop attacking and try to cast you have to wait a certain time before you can begin to cast again. To use quick-cast you have to click it then wait for it to be ready then cast ONE spell after that you have to click quick-cast again and repeat.
<br />

<br />

<br />
In the middle of a fight the EQ magic system is 10000% better than doac, but as far as user friendlyness outside of actual combat I'd have to give it to doac.
<br />

<br />

<br />
so far, I like doac, its not good enough to keep me away from planes of power or good events on stormhammer, but it is a great game to fill my weekdays when I don't have enough time to invest in EQ.
<br />

<br />

<br />
#1 problem with EQ: Time sinks. doac moves along without the enormous boring time sinks.
<br />
#1 problem with doac: The entire game has an extremly sluggish feel to it. EQ's controll interface is like a crisp sportscar, compared to doac's overwieght transit bus.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
