				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">LOL!!
<br />

<br />

<br />
There is no comparison between EQ casters and DOAC casters. DOAC is so far superior to EQ in almost every aspect. Firstly, no mind numbbing arse sitting endlessly to regain mana: secondly, DOAC graphics are so much better and generate less lag (I cringe remembering the lag in places like HKH or on Planes raids when one spell cast would paralyze the entire raiding party): third, you don't have to sell your sister to get the platt to buy the spells you need later in the game, nor do you have to sell your mother to get those items you need to be uber enough to cast those mana eating spells once you find them: fourth, you have choices in spell lines, eg the cleric, whose roles can be broadened yet still remain the main healer in a group: fifth and most importantly, you can develop your character the way you want to...your path is not set in stone...not all clerics operate the same, not all wizzies operate the same, etc. Everyone behind the keyboard brings a new approach to gaming in DAOC whereas EQ loves the cookiecutter players. 
<br />

<br />
~tosses her necro robe and scythe into the trash~
