			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I dont think you guys played EQ very long
<br />

<br />
I played DAOC beta and I tried it again on the new PVP servers, and I have played EQ since it came out, and other than the downtime, which EQ has since repaired, there is NO comparison between the smoothness, and your abiltiy to improve your spellcasting in EQ and the crap DAOC tries to pass off as a Magic system.
<br />

<br />
In EQ a caster under attack has the ability to recover concentration (a learned skill) and still cast, in DAOC you are stuck with a quickcast timer and cause this sucked so bad they added another realm skill, which still doesnt fix the problem.
<br />

<br />
In EQ LOS will block a spell, in DAOC all a caster has to do is hit the Auto Attack key and he is protected from bolts.  In EQ pets have the same restrictions as their masters, in DAOC chanter pets run wild and can cast while under attack.
<br />

<br />
In DAOC I can snare a level 49 character with a level 9 one, hello resistance system.
<br />
I cant snare a level 11 mob half the time.
<br />

<br />
So okay I picked a Mana Eldritch, maybe I just dont play it right, but someone want to tell me what I have to defend myself with against attack? 
<br />

<br />
It sure isnt any spell in my spell book = P</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
